Description: Fragment of body of East Greek pottery open vessel, probably a cup. Inside streakily glazed; exterior reserved, probably the handle zone. Graffito inscription on exterior. Very fine soft fabric.
Curator's comments: The sherd appears to be East Greek but its typology cannot be assessed from the available photograph. The text is not found among those published in Petrie 1886 and not as yet located. (new photos confirm EG, but typology still not easy.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.671)
